<h2 id="Syntax" name="Syntax">Syntax</h2>

<pre class="twopartsyntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code><a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="Possible values: a number followed by'em', 'ex', 'ch', 'rem', 'px', 'cm', 'mm', 'in', 'vh', 'vw', 'vmin', 'vmax', 'pt', 'pc' or 'px', like 3px, 1.5cm, -0.5em or 0">&lt;length&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Single_bar" title="Single bar: The two entities are optional, but exactly one must be present.">|</a> auto</code>
</pre>

<pre>column-width: auto
column-width: 6px     /* Different &lt;length&gt; values */
column-width: 25em
column-width: 0.3vw

column-width: inherit
</pre>

<h3 id="Values">Values</h3>

<dl><dt><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> value giving a hint of the optimal width of the column. The actual column width may be wider (to fill the available space), or narrower (only if the available space is smaller than the specified column width). The length must be strictly positive or the declaration is invalid.</dd>
 <dt><code>auto</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a keyword indicating that the width of the column should be determined by other CSS properties, like <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/column-count" title="The column-count CSS property describes the number of columns of the element."><code>column-count</code></a>.</dd>
</dl>